Found in many lakes and ponds, ducks are a common site the world over. Known for their famous quack, ducks tend to congregate in flocks or go off on their own in pairs. The vet said he had brain swelling and neurological damage. so, how he did this, i don't know and i'm freakin' pissed off because now i have to put him down. why do my babies die( if you don't know me, i love all animals and treat them as if they are my children so to speak)? It breaks me heart.

Last night i was having one of those nights where you just think of everything and anything.
I started thinking about the little pleasures i enjoy, so i've decided to share them with you
and hope you would share some with me.
1. The soft feel of my legs after a shave
2. Working in my little garden
3. Having my kitty and puppy
4. Getting magazines and even junk mail in the mail.
5. Walking out to get the mail. (it's like an obsession)
6. The sound of the dishwasher
7. Finding an amazing sale (in all areas!)
8. sounds corny- but i love walking on the beach, close to the water or ankle deep
9. finally getting that beauty idea in a magazine right
10. A shower radio :)

Unlike-able things

Stinky seaweed/water smell
Not fully erasing stuff on the board
Repeating myself
Being splashed
The TV/ Radio/ Peoples voices, and anything else that is loud
Contradicting me when i am positively right
Surprises
My Uncle Jim in every aspect
Days over 70 degrees and under 55
yeh... enough is enough


<3 Anna

So i have been keeping occupied. My dad had a hip replacement surgery and i have become the resident nurse
and caregiver with the help of mom and lissa of course. It actually takes a lot outa ya. i miss everyone and wish i could be out there. Sometime this month i want to go to Wild Waves. I need someone to drive me there....i might go with the Baglio's but that is still undecided. Been reading some good books lately, a series really....Abram's Daughters. Its about the amish, very interesting i might add. well i'm babbling.... bye

So my day yesterday went from doing completely nothing to the most busy i've ever been. hard transition but i made it. them my dad decides we are going to a mariners game. it was fabulous. we bought cheep tickets and didn't even sit in them we sat in box office seats because rosie had 1 and we were with her...actually i don't know how it reall worked out. i wondered around for a bit, sat behind home plate for a while. that place is just so much fun. iswear i have never seen so many cute guys in one place. aren't i the lucky one.most of them had girlfriends though. meh. anywho, got home at 11 and went straight to bed. woke up this morning and got ready to come to my once again boring job that i honestly love to come to. i am so happy it is nice todayi have big windows by my desk that let the sun in and give my a great landscaped view. well i love and miss y'all.

Anna

Today our little Pixy kitty was burried just a few hours ago. By word of my uncle, she was attacked. He was kind enough to lay her in a box so we would not see the mutalated body of our beloved little girl. It is my sisters cat and she i wrought with grief. We will miss her funny antics and loving ways. <3

In the morning i arrive at work and find that my computer monitor isn't working. bad. this is a essential tool. so i had to set up office in the supervisors room. everything was hectict until around 1 the tech guy came and fixed it...funny thought because i didn't need it then because i was going to leave at 2.

after work mom drive me to the ferry to meet up with the Baglio's, Javan, and Elisa. upon arriving in seattle we head down to a place called the Melting Pot. It's a fondu place. Food was nummy but desert was the best. afterwards we went to see the play Grease at the Paramount. My first play and first time in the paramount. that place is gorgeous. And of all the people i see Pip and her gang there! :)Fun! Frankie Avalon was there(he sings beauty school drop-out). After the play Brennen, Javan, Cassondra, and I walk to the car while The others went to the truck. Brennen driving in the midst of Seattle traffic- uhg. Every time they saw a showgirls sign they would crack up histarically. well we missed the ferry so then we take the highway. Brennen was driving really fast and me and cassondra stuck our heads out the window and let our hair fly. Javan did this also but afterwards he had an afro! Me and cassondra fell asleep for a while. Brennen kindly drove me home, even after all the horrible directions i gave him. I arrived home at 12:16. and here i am at work again with a good 6 hours of sleep. hah! 

Ecited for Survivor Finale and Grey's anatomy! woohoo.

Your Birthdate: April 25
Your birth on the 25th day of the month (7 energy) modifies your life path by giving you some special interest in technical, scientific, or other complex and often hard to understand subjects. You may become something of a perfectionist and a stickler for details. Your thinking is logical and intuitive, rational and responsible. Your feelings may run deep, but you are not very likely to let them show. This birthday makes you a more private person, more introspective and perhaps more inflexible. In friendships you are very cautious and reserved. You are probably inventive, and given to unique approaches and solutions.
